Table 1. Comparison with state-of-the-art methods of the holistic re-ID problem. The 
1 st /2 nd results are shown in red/blue, respectively. The methods in the 1st group are 
rigid stripe based. The methods in the 2nd group are auto-localization based. The 3rd 
group is attention based methods. The methods in the 4th group are extra semantic 
based. The last line is our method

Table 2. Comparison with state-of-the-art methods of the occluded re-ID problem on 
Occluded-DukeMTMC. Methods in the 1st group are for the holistic re-ID problem. 
Methods in the 2nd group utilize extra pose information for occluded re-ID problem. 
The methods in the 3rd group do not adopt extra semantic. The last line is our method
